	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002072_0001"><!--pb/@n='80r'--></pb>
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName><settlement type="town">Clifton</settlement></placeName> <date when="1864-09-24">24<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Sept<hi rend="sup">r</hi></abbr><expan>September</expan></choice>
<lb/>1864</date></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My dear <persName>Waller</persName></p>
<lb/><p>May I trust
<lb/>to your generosity to
<lb/>send me a double
<lb/>copy of your black
<lb/>photographs instead
<lb/>of one as I wish
<lb/>to present <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">them</add> from
<lb/>you to <persName>Miss Watson</persName>
<lb/>I said I would ask 
<lb/>you - so now do 
<lb/>if you can send them

	

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002072_0002"><!--pb/@n='80v'--></pb>
<lb/>to <placeName>Newstead Abbey</placeName>
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="town">Mansfield</settlement></placeName> at your
<lb/>convenience -</p>
<lb/><p>I saw poor <choice><sic><persName>Speke</persName>s</sic><corr><persName>Speke</persName>'s</corr></choice>
<lb/>remains conveyed
<lb/>to their resting place
<lb/>yesterday - there
<lb/>were no sobs so
<lb/>loud as the <unclear cert="medium">poetical</unclear>
<lb/>reported or penny a
<lb/>liner reported - 
<lb/>nor did <persName>Grant</persName> who
<lb/>is a fine fellow &amp;
<lb/>a <term type="person">Scotchman</term> the
<lb/>equivalent of all

	

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002072_0003"><!--pb/@n='81r'--></pb>
<lb/><choice><sic>thats<corr>that's</corr></sic></choice> good &amp;c &amp;c. go
<lb/>down into the 
<lb/>vault - He put a
<lb/>small "<term type="plant"><hi rend="underline">immortelle</hi></term>"
<lb/>of <term type="plant">violets</term> &amp; <term type="plant">mignonette</term>
<lb/>on the coffin as
<lb/>it was borne past
<lb/>us in the church
<lb/>so much for
<lb/>contemporary history</p>

<lb/><cb rend="vertical"/>
<lb/><ab rend="no-indent"><hi rend="double-underline" hand="#U"><persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> <choice><orig>Livingston</orig><reg>Livingstone</reg></choice></persName></hi></ab>
<lb/>
			

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002072_0004"><!--pb/@n='81v'--></pb><!-- Bleedthrough from recto side of page and previous page's verso HB 9/25/12 -->
